x^8-256 &= (x^4)^2-(16)^2\\
&=(x^4-16)(x^4+16).
\end{align*}The second factor can be written as the difference of squares $(x^2)^2-(4)^2$. So the expression can be factored even further: \[(x^4-16)(x^4+16)=(x^4-16)(x^2+4)(x^2-4).\]The expression $x^2-4$ can also be factored as a difference of squares. Written in this new form, the expression $x^8-256$ can be completely factored as \begin{align*}
x^8-256 &= (x^4-16)(x^2+4)(x^2-4)\\
&=\boxed{(x^4-16)(x^2+4)(x-2)(x+2)}.
\end{align*}
